Gulf Stocks: Air Arabia, First Gulf Bank and Kingdom Holding

-- B y   Z a h r a   H a n k i r
-- 
2011-02-22T14:28:35Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-22/gulf-stocks-air-arabia-first-gulf-bank-and-kingdom-holding.html
Dubai’s  DFM General Index  lost 2.4
percent to 1,479.41, the lowest since Aug. 16 at the 2 p.m.
close in the emirate. Qatar’s QE Index slumped 3.6 percent and
Saudi Arabia’s index lost 0.4 percent.  The following stocks rose or fell in the Gulf. Symbols are
in parentheses.        Air Arabia  PJSC (AIRARABI UH) dropped for a second day this
week, retreating 1.5 percent to 81.3 fils. The Middle East’s
biggest low-cost airline said full-year profit declined 32
percent to 309.6 million dirhams ($84.3 million).        First Gulf Bank PJSC  (FGB UH) decreased to the lowest since
Oct. 24, tumbling 6.1 percent to 16.1 dirhams. The lender
controlled by Abu Dhabi’s ruling family listed 125 million new
shares on the Abu Dhabi stock exchange after converting 3.6
billion dirhams of convertible bonds.        Kingdom Holding Co . (KINGDOM AB) rose the most in two
weeks, jumping 7.5 percent to 9.35 riyals. Saudi billionaire
Prince Alwaleed Bin Talal, the controller of the investment
company, yesterday said its real-estate projects are “solid
anchors” for its profitability.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Zahra Hankir in Dubai at 
 zhankir@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
